text:
â€¢ hey everyone! I am busy working on the CMS for Developers Practicum and I am stuck on Must be at least 3 columns on large screens with at least one media query to change layout to 2 columns on screens below 900 pixels
My code currently looks like this


module.html(HTML+Hubl)
  &lt;div class="container "&gt;
        {% for item in module.field_group %}
    &lt;div class="item  "&gt;
	{% if item.employee_image.src %}
		{% set sizeAttrs = 'width="{{ item.employee_image.width }}" height="{{ item.employee_image.height }}"' %}
		{% if item.employee_image.size_type == 'auto' %}
			{% set sizeAttrs = 'width="{{ item.employee_image.width }}" height="{{ item.employee_image.height }}" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;"' %}
		{% elif item.employee_image.size_type == 'auto_custom_max' %}
			{% set sizeAttrs = 'width="{{ item.employee_image.max_width }}" height="{{ item.employee_image.max_height }}" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;"' %}
		{% endif %}
		 {% set loadingAttr = item.employee_image.loading != 'disabled' ? 'loading="{{ item.employee_image.loading }}"' : '' %}
		&lt;img src="{{ item.employee_image.src }}" alt="{{ item.employee_image.alt }}" {{ loadingAttr }} {{ sizeAttrs }}&gt;
	{% endif %}
	{% inline_rich_text field="employee_name" value="{{ item.employee_name }}" %}
	{% inline_text field="employee_role" value="{{ item.employee_role }}" %}
    &lt;/div&gt;

{% endfor %}
      &lt;/div&gt;

Module.css
.item{
width:100%;}

.item:last-child{
  margin-right:0}

.container{
  display: flex;
  width:100%;
 column-count: 3;
 column-width: 100px;

}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .column {
  column-span: 6;
}




I have looked into a lot , css, flexbox and watching a couple videos but I just cant get the media query to work. Is it due to me using a loop? I saw that someone gave an answer regarding an older practicum for this course where it was 4 columns and then 2 . I am getting frustrated as I know its something VERY simple

Hey  <@U03JY8J1WSD> , try this.

```.container{ width: 100%; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }

.container .item{ width: calc( 25% - 30px ); }

@media( max-width: 900px ){
 .container .item{ width: calc( 50% - 10px ) }
}```
